1. create a component using class

	1) define a class
		class TagName extends React.Component {
		..........
		}

	2) build the constructor
		constructor(props) {
			super(props);
			this.state=obj; // the state is an object

			use bind method to pass this. to self-define methods
		}

	3) render(){
		....
		return a component element
		}

	4) self-defined methods



2. state property:
	
	1) state is an object
	2) we intiialize the state in constructor
	3) use this.setState(newState) method to change the state (pass the new object as the parameter)
	4) get the properties in the state: this.state.propName



if we have state property, we must use class to create obj, otherwise we can consider using function